I’ll just take the whole wheelbarrow full thanks.

Ice days are for thinking deep thoughts and putting things out in the universe. I’d love for your input on any and all below…

1) Teaching - I love to teach! I’m hoping to do more in person events here in Austin (plus I’ll be teaching at Craftcation this spring). I’m working on some online course ideas too. What would you like to take? Do you prefer in person or online?

2) @creativequeso podcast. I put out my last episode with @natterdoodles right before the pandemic. Now I’m debating bringing it back. Did you ever listen? I’m brainstorming guest ideas. If by some whim I found a sponsor and brought it back who should I interview?

3) Hey fellow art journalers - do you buy printables? The collage packs in my @jenniferperkinsart Etsy store sell so well I was thinking about a download version.

4) Bookity books! I’ve got a new kids craft book coming out this spring. I’m still working on my romance novel (40k words in whoo-hoo) now I need an agent then a publisher, but that’s jumping ahead. My question is what are your thoughts on a Kitschmas coffee table book? Pictures of my house decked out through the years and maybe some crafts? I’m looking into self publishing this one. Though a publisher would be more awesome.

Ok off to ponder the lint in my belly button and continue pontificating.

Oh and this is a collage and watercolor piece I made. Lesson from @cre8tivecre8tions in @willowing Lifebook class.

Today my 4th book hit Amazon - welcome to the world Paper and Tape Crafts! Sure it’s for kids but I promise there are some adult worthy projects too if you want to grab a copy for you and your little to share. 

If you’ve got paper, scissors, tape and some cardboard you’re well on your way to making flip books, games galore, masks, snakes and more. Throw in some old magazines, brown lunch bags and a paper plate and things get extra crazy crafty !

In the immortal words of @poison - my trip to California was nothin’ but a good time. I taught 5 workshops at this year’s Craftcation including: Painting Weirdos, Leather Scrap Jewelry, Spicing Up Craft Store Beads and Making Your Art Wearable. I saw old friends and made bunches of new ones. Visited 3.5 galleries including: @thebroadmuseum @craftcontemporary @basquiatkingpleasure and a walk through the courtyard of @lacma on the way to lunch. Plus I ate at fancy restaurants, put my feet in the ocean and had an impromptu photo shoot at the strip mall where ZZ Top filmed their Legs video. Not bad for a 4 night trip.
.
.
.
#craftcation #artretreat #craftcation23 #craftretreat #craftcation2023 #instatravel #crafty #artsyfartsy #craftclasses #artclasses

I’m going to brush my hair and get out of my pajamas not once BUT twice in the next few weeks and you’re invited! Let’s get virtually crafty together to celebrate!

Marketing For Makers Wednesday July 12th 3:15pm CST - This fabulous two day virtual event is brought to you by @dearhandmadelife and @constantcontact lots of great info and I’ll be hosting a virtual Painting Weirdos Workshop! It’s free so grab some paint and cardboard and let’s let those crafty freak flags fly!

The Great Bead Extravaganza Midsummer Market Sunday July 23rd 4:30pm CST Another fabulous free two day virtual event brought to you by @thegreatbeadextravaganza ! During my 1 hour slot I’ll be talking about all the ways you can transform wooden craft store beads. We’ll be burning, painting, dying and more so please do stop in and hang out!

If you’ve missed my weekly Facebook Lives this is our chance to reconnect! Swipe through to get an idea of what we will be making and I can’t wait to see you there! Links to both events in my profile!
.

Did someone say GIVEAWAY? Yup, keep reading. I’ve teamed up with @slice_cuts for some creepy cute fun! 

When Slice sent me a box full of tools including a brand spanking new box cutter complete with fancy ceramic blade I knew exactly what I wanted to make. One stack of cardboard boxes later and I’ve got my new favorite #halloweenwithjen prop!

Slice tools cut through cardboard, paper, fabric and even pink fun fur! Wanna win a box of your own craft goodies from Slice? Sure you do!

All you gotta do is follow me and @slice_cuts then leave a comment here about what you would love to make with your very own set of Slice tools. Everything from craft knives and retractable precision cutters for paper to scissors and seam rippers for fabric.
